    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the pan to a medium-high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> (there should be some juices leftover from the beef strips), add the <strong>sliced shallot</strong>,<strong> garlic</strong> and <strong>ginger</strong> and cook for 1-2 min or until softened</p><p>Meanwhile, grate the <strong>apple<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> (skin on)</p><p>Once softened, add the <strong>grated apple </strong>then the<strong> mirin </strong>and cook for 2-3 min or until the apple starts to break down</p>",
